Now you've taken a look around the mystery files, it's time to start collecting clues.

Have a read of the "crimescene" file.

It's a pretty long file - The officers on the scene are meticulous, and have written down EVERYTHING in their officer reports.

Fortunately the sergeant went through and marked the real clues with "CLUE" so it would be easy to find them again.

Your first challenge is to search the file for these clues, then output them to a "clues.txt" file.

Once you've got the clues, move onto "step2"
